Biography

GALLERY

Junior (2007-08): Played all 28 games, started 14 ... was inserted into the starting lineup against Robert Morris (11/24), which paid instant dividends as she scored a season-high 11 points and four boards ... split time between starting and coming off the bench during conference play ... her best game in Sun Belt action was a 10-point effort as she played 27 minutes off the bench against Troy ... also grabbed eight rebounds in the Owls win over FIU (2/21).

Junior College (North Dakota State College of Science): Played for Paulette Stein ... named First Team All-American and First Team All-Conference her sophomore season ... earned Second Team All-Conference her freshman season.

High School: Attended Park Center High School ... played for Patty Sorensen ... earned All-Conference honors twice during her prep career.

Personal: Sociology major ... born Oct. 17, 1987, in St. Paul, Minn. ... daughter of Joan and John Momoh.
